\centering
\includegraphics[width=3.4in]{Figure3_New.eps} 
\DeclareGraphicsExtensions.
\caption{PSDs of NC-OFDM and the low-interference scheme with varying \emph{N} and \emph{L}.}
  \label{Fig3}
\end{figure}




Fig. \ref{Fig4} shows the BER performance of NC-OFDM, NCSP-OFDM, and the low-interference scheme when \emph{N}=3 and \emph{L}=$M_{\rm cp}$=144  in 3GPP LTE EVA fading channel. It is shown that traditional NC-OFDM will introduce severe  interference to the transmit signal and hence to influence the BER performance, while NCSP-OFDM and our proposed low-interference scheme can both effectively mitigate the interference so as to achieve similar BER performance to OFDM, and to save the complexity for signal recovery at the receiver. However, the proposed low-interference scheme is with much lower complexity compared to other schemes according to Table I. In general, we show that the proposed scheme can make a promising tradeoff among BER performance, sidelobe suppression performance and computational complexity. 

